The program must accept an integer N as the input.
The program must print the desired pattern as shown in the Example Input/Output sections.
Boundary Condition(s):
2 <= N <= 32
Example Input/Output 1:
Input: 4 
Output:
a
B c
D e F
g H i J
Example Input/Output 2: 
Input: 8
Output:
a
B c
D e F
g H i J
k L m N o
P q R s T u
V w X y Z a B
c D e F g H i J
#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>

int main()
{
    //a=0,B=1,c=2,D=3
    //alphabet at even position are in lower case
    //alphabet at odd position are in upper case 
    int N;
    int ctr=0;//control
    scanf("%d",&N);
    for(int row=0;row<N;row++)
    {
        for(int col=0;col<N;col++)
        {
            if(ctr%2==0)
            //for to check Z it is not possible because count 0 to 25 so for that add %26 to ctr
            {
                printf("%c", ctr%26+'a'); 
            }
            else
            {
                printf("%c",ctr%26+'A'); 
            }
            ctr++;
        }
    }

}

//ternary operator printf("%c",ctr%2==0?ctr%26+'a':ctr%26+'A');
